---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "@components/Button.astro";
const title = 'When to Call Me';
const description = 'Concrete decision triggers and a bounded next step for requesting an independent architectural verdict on SAP BTP.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <section class="stack tight">
    <h1>When to call me</h1>
    <p class="measure">Decision triggers and protocol for requesting external architectural judgment. Formal, minimal, and outcome‑oriented.</p>
  </section>

  <h2>Decision triggers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No team can legitimately approve the required change end‑to‑end.</li>
    <li>The issue is still being worked on, but the decision no longer converges.</li>
    <li>Multiple teams are locally correct, but the architecture remains globally unstable.</li>
    <li>Rollout or security hardening is exposing assumptions that should have been settled before.</li>
    <li>Surface‑level success but runtime inconsistency across entry paths (e.g., App Router, Work Zone).</li>
    <li>Tenant variance appearing during onboarding or expansion.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why continuing internally may feel safer — and still increase risk</h2>
  <p class="measure">Continuing with familiar delivery motions lowers friction but not risk. When the problem is jurisdiction across boundaries, more implementation activity delays the decision while deepening the wrong contract.</p>

  <h2>What you probably do not need me for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Staffing on implementation or delivery tickets.</li>
    <li>Low‑level troubleshooting with clear ownership already established.</li>
    <li>Generic advisory without a concrete architectural decision to make.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to send</h2>
  <p class="measure">Send a structured summary including:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Landscape — S/4 + BTP runtime(s) + identity surfaces</li>
    <li>Observable runtime divergence — what works where; what fails where</li>
    <li>Timeline — go‑live, rollout, and recent changes</li>
    <li>Stakeholder ownership — who holds what today</li>
    <li>The decision that cannot converge</li>
  </ol>
  <div style="display:flex; gap:.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <Button href="mailto:pei_jiandong@hotmail.com" variant="primary">Send structured summary</Button>
    <Button href="/work/" variant="ghost">See engagement formats</Button>
  </div>

  <h2>What happens next</h2>
  <p class="measure">I confirm whether the situation matches a boundary failure pattern. If appropriate, we proceed with a fixed‑scope triage, audit, or verdict — defined in writing, time‑bounded, and outcome‑specific. Where executive‑level convergence is required, the Executive Boundary Verdict defines final jurisdiction.</p>

  <p>For the model behind this assessment, see the <a href="/boundary-model/">Boundary Model</a>. For essays, see <a href="/insights/">Insights</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
